      <description>I'm not going to bother to quote and add another color, since I only have one relevant block of text to respond to.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As far as I know, EQ still uses that encryption.  For this reason, ShowEQ does &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; packet sniff anymore.  It reads from EQ's memory space, then an external program connects to it across TCP (same or any other computer).  It updates that program, which interprets everything and basically acts as the front end.  That's what a ShowEQ user is going to be looking at.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;On a side note, regular ShowEQ runs on Linux.  A quick google of "MySEQ" will turn up the Windows version.</description>
