      <title>Re: What is Sony doing about exploit/cheaters?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=111014#M111014</link>
      <description>&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Floppie7th wrote:&lt;BR&gt;As far as I know, EQ still uses that encryption. For this reason, ShowEQ does &lt;B&gt;not&lt;/B&gt; packet sniff anymore. It reads from EQ's memory space, then an external program connects to it across TCP (same or any other computer). It updates that program, which interprets everything and basically acts as the front end. That's what a ShowEQ user is going to be looking at.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;On a side note, regular ShowEQ runs on Linux. A quick google of "MySEQ" will turn up the Windows version.&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;EQ does use encryption.&amp;nbsp;Most of my information comes from a slashdot article done at the time the encryption was changed and from searching thier message board, at around PoP, they went to a public/private key. It forced ShowEQ to go to a keysniffer that ran on the EQ machine and sent the key back to the linux machine. At some point, EQ changed back to the old style&amp;nbsp;encryption which allowed them to brute force the key and did not need the external program any more. It does sniff the packets, and decrypts them on the fly so it is totally passive again.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;A href="http://features.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=02/12/01/1558220&amp;amp;tid=9&amp;amp;tid=10" target=_blank&gt;http://features.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=02/12/01/1558220&amp;amp;tid=9&amp;amp;tid=10&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;That is the slashdot article from Dec '02.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;ShowEQ looks pretty much dead now. It still functions, but a lot of its features have been incorporated into EQ already and doesn't seem to have much activity any more.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As a side note, my quote about having Sony pay me came off wrong. What I was trying to say, I will provide them with what is freely available, if there are any costs, like that one site selling plugins or to gain access to the "VIP" section of MQ, that they pay me for the expenses occured to get them any additional plugins/scripts.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
